## For darulquran.pk

### Trust & content (E-E-A-T)
- Org JSON-LD in root layout; article authors and dates on posts
- HTTPS + security headers; contact info from Sanity `siteSettings`
- One H1 per page; Urdu `alt` on images; internal links across courses ↔ services ↔ articles
- Concise Urdu intros, lists, FAQs for SGE; `llms.txt` for AI crawlers
- No keyword stuffing, cloaking, dark patterns, or misleading metadata

### Core Web Vitals (mobile-first index)
| Metric | Target | Detail rules |
|--------|--------|--------------|
| LCP | ≤2.5s | `09-technical-seo-mobile.mdc` · `optimize-lcp` skill |
| INP | ≤200ms | Lazy mobile nav; light handlers |
| CLS | ≤0.1 | Image dimensions; reserved hero space |

Test **both** Lighthouse Mobile and Desktop (`10-technical-seo-desktop.mdc`).

### Schema & metadata
- `components/seo/*` + `pageMetadata()` — JSON-LD must match visible title/description
- Canonical via `pageMetadata({ path })`; `robots.ts` + `sitemap.ts`

### Accessibility & engagement
- Skip link; keyboard nav dropdowns; `role="menuitem"` inside menus only
- Touch targets ≥44px (`TW_TOUCH` in `lib/tailwind.ts`)
- Clear above-fold intent; no intrusive interstitials

### UI performance (Tailwind)
- Pure utilities — no CSS-in-JS; shared patterns in `lib/tailwind.ts` (`06-tailwind.mdc`)
- Below-fold: `TW_CV_AUTO` (`content-visibility: auto`)
- Rich text: `rich-text` classes — not broken `prose-*`
- Hero LCP: inline styles only for `--hero-delay` and blur placeholder

### Production
- Next.js on port **3001** (`12-production-port.mdc`); deploy via `11-deploy-ops.mdc`
- On-demand CMS revalidation via Sanity webhook (`setup-revalidation` skill)
- Contact form: rate-limited, Zod-validated (`17-security.mdc`)
